org.kramerlab.vines

Class Graph

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.kramerlab.vines.Graph

  • public class Graph
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represents a Graph for the RVine.
    One Graph represents one dimension of the RVine.
    It uses the Node and Edge classes. The Edges got put in as directed, but they get mirrored automatically to get an undirected Graph.
    Author:
    Christian Lamberty (clamber@students.uni-mainz.de)

        public Node addNode(int name)
        Adds a Node to the Node list by its integer representation.
        Only works for Nodes in dimension 1 to simplify the addition.
        Initializes a row in the adjacency list for the added Node.
        Parameters:
        name - The integer label to be added as Node.
        Returns:
        returns the constructed Node with the given name.

      • addEdge

        public void addEdge(Edge e)
        Adds an Edge to the Graph.
        The Edge needs to be initialized with a from-Node and a to-Node.
        A mirrored Edge will be added automatically to create an undirected Edge.
        Parameters:
        e - The Edge to be added.

      • addEdge

        public void addEdge(Node from,
                    Node to,
                    double weight)
        Adds an Edge to the Graph by a from Node, a to Node and an Edge weight.
        A mirrored Edge will be added automatically to create an undirected Edge.
        Parameters:
        from - a Node where the Edge comes from.
        to - a Node where the Edge goes to.
        weight - the Kendall't tau value as weight.
